theorem
fixes h :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall>x. h x = sqrt ((x powr 3 + 72) / 2) + 1"
shows  "h 6 = 13"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 If $h(x) = \sqrt{\frac{x^3+72}{2}}+1$, what is the value of $h(6)$? The final Answer is 13
 ### Proof

 *)

fixes h :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
